{"source_key":"sha256-a74ceb5e1c9633ab993c14c11d587d71","record_index":25,"record_hash":"sha256:9acac548a7a51417f7cca5344c371f1df28210ee487cd62780e2a1930e6323e6","timestamp":"2026-05-20T19:01:46.446Z","kind":"tool_result","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:function_call_output","role":null,"text":"Chunk ID: e0af1d\nWall time: 0.0000 seconds\nProcess exited with code 0\nOriginal token count: 2587\nOutput:\nThat keeps the common prompt easy:\n\n```text\nCheck whether there are prior agent sessions related to this branch and catch up.\n```\n\nThe CLI can keep storage terms like `session_key` and `turn_key` internally, but\nhuman-facing help should prefer `session id` and `turn id`. \"Key\" reads like an\nimplementation detail.\n\n### `sessions`\n\nPurpose: answer \"what sessions should I inspect?\"\n\nTargeted form:\n\n```text\nbut agentlog sessions branch agentlog-turn-storage\n```\n\nUntargeted form:\n\n```text\nbut agentlog sessions --limit 10\n```\n\nThe targeted form returns sessions related to a branch, review, or change. The\nuntargeted form returns recent project sessions. Both should return compact\norientation data.\n\nJSON should include:\n\n- requested target, if any\n- `session_key`\n- `updated_at`\n- `started_at`, if known\n- `turn_count`\n- `record_count`\n- `related_turn_keys`, only for targeted lookup\n- match evidence, not confidence:\n  - `matched_by`, for example `branch_observed`, `review_observed`,\n    `change_observed`, or `explicit_reference`\n  - `matched_turn_keys`\n  - other observed branch/review/change keys, when present\n- source metadata: agents, providers, models, tool versions\n- latest turn key and latest capture timestamp\n- latest user/assistant excerpts, when cheap to derive\n\nThis command should not hydrate transcript records. It is an index card.\nIt should be sorted by most recent activity first.\n\n### `timeline`\n\nPurpose: answer \"what happened across this session, and which turns look worth\nreading?\"\n\nExample:\n\n```text\nbut agentlog timeline sha256-9d942495afce65d863ef4d05e61ce2da --limit 20\n```\n\nJSON should include one entry per capture turn:\n\n- stable turn index within the session\n- `turn_key`\n- `previous_turn_key`\n- `capture_kind`\n- `captured_at`\n- `record_count`\n- record index range\n- environment snapshot status\n- observed branch/review/change target keys\n- first and last record timestamps\n- tiny previews of the fi\n[TRUNCATED]\nider session id but overlapping\n  prior conversation context\n\nAvoid hard-coding those labels until the source data supports them. For now,\nexpose enough facts for the consuming agent to decide.\n\n## Non-Goals\n\n- no provider-native resume\n- no generated persistent handoff summary\n- no magic `handoff` command for v1\n- no durable inferred ownership like \"this branch belongs to this session\"\n- no GitButler app API dependency for the first flow\n- no automatic transcript dumping into `but status`\n- no product-specific review browsing payloads\n\n## Open Questions\n\n- Do we need a first-class \"session outline\" primitive in `but-agentlog`, or can\n  it be assembled cheaply from existing reads?\n- Can we reliably capture provider metadata that distinguishes top-level\n  sessions from spawned subagents?\n- Should compaction/resume grouping be a later derived feature, or do we need to\n  store more source metadata now to make it possible?\n- How much transcript text should human-readable output show by default?\n\n## Recommended First Implementation Slice\n\nDo not implement \"handoff\" as one magic command.\n\nFirst add enough generic CLI read commands that an agent or skill can perform the\ncatch-up workflow:\n\n1. enhance `agentlog sessions` so JSON includes session outline fields, not just\n   keys\n2. add a bounded timeline command for one session\n3. add a bounded records command for one turn\n4. write a small skill/workflow note that tells agents how to use those commands\n\nThat keeps the feature honest. If the workflow feels clumsy after using the\nprimitives on real branches, improve the primitives rather than hiding them\nbehind an opaque command.\n\n## Rough Build Plan\n\nBuild this as small, reviewable slices. Do not change storage unless a slice\nproves the current storage cannot support the command cleanly.\n\n### Slice 1: Richer `sessions`\n\nGoal: answer \"which related sessions should I inspect first?\"\n\nKeep the existing command shape:\n\n```text\nbut agentlog sessions [branch [<branch>] | review <review> | change <change>] [--limit N]\n```\n\n","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-20T19:01:46.446Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]"}}}